sentences: Sarah Louise Whatmore (born 21 September 1981) is an English singer-songwriter, best known for appearing in the first series of the British TV series Pop Idol.
In 2002 and 2003 she released two singles "When I Lost You" and "Automatic", respectively, which both reached the Top 20 in the UK Singles Chart.
In 2008, she came up with an album of new material.
The first single was titled "Smile", and was released on 22 September 2008.
The album, Time To Think, was released on 23 March 2009.
In 2016 Whatmore started to officially release music again and published 3 tracks throughout the year, Whatmore released her first EP Full Circle on 24 March 2016.

Several recordings were leaked over the years, including "Close To Me" and "Don't Let Me Go".
Turning down the opportunity to become a backing singer for Kylie Minogue to concentrate on her own solo career, Whatmore spent the next five years honing her craft.
During the years she wrote more than two hundred songs with various collaborators including Greg Fitzgerald and Peter John Vettese.
